      <h1 class='title'>Coalminers' Compensation Scheme</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1721WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1721ws' title='Col. 1721WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1721WS' name='column_1721ws' href='#column_1721ws' rel='bookmark'>1721WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_413'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-taylor' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_413' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Taylor' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-taylor" title="Mr David Taylor">David Taylor</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">To ask the Secretary of State for Trade and Industry when she expects to reach the last decile of registered coal compensation claims for<span class="italic">(a)</span> chronic obstructive pulmonary disease and <span class="italic">(b)</span> vibration white finger for former miners or their widows or families in the east Midlands.[189188]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_414'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-nigel-griffiths' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_414' title='Link to this speech by Mr Nigel Griffiths' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-nigel-griffiths" title="Mr Nigel Griffiths">Nigel Griffiths</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The Department is currently holding detailed discussions on chronic obstructive pulmonary disease and plans to report progress to Sir Michael Turner, the judge who oversees the respiratory scheme, later this month when he visits the DTI's claims handlers. On claims for VWF, the Department aims to have completed all general damages offers by the end of 2004, and to have all claims settled by the end of 2005.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
